      "writtenOn": "2021-01-14T19:11:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m so used to negative signs showing up on xy, yx, and dy that it makes me concerned not to see them here. Generally speaking OpenType has always been y-up and FreeType has reflected that in reporting everything y-up. Skia is y-down, so we end up negating the right column here. It seems that the ides is to do this in neutralizeUpemTransform which itself seems weird?\n\nAlso, just formatting wise, if the arguments all started on the following line (indented four) then it would be nice to get them three to a line since we tend to think of it as 3x3.\n\n    return SkMatrix::MakeAll(\n        SkFixedToScalar(affine23.xx), SkFixedToScalar(affine23.xy), SkFixedToScalar(affine23.dx),\n        SkFixedToScalar(affine23.yx), SkFixedToScalar(affine23.yy), SkFixedToScalar(affine23.dy),\n        0, 0, 1);",
      "revId": "85b37637cbc8e77babcc641bad511013f1b608ea",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bacdcec8_9c922bcb",
