      "writtenOn": "2021-01-14T19:11:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Inverting is really bad (numerically) and slow. I think maybe it works out to just doing a few divides here because we special case scale only matrices, but \u0027invert\u0027 always smells to me. Literally anything we can do to avoid this would be better. I am somewhat baffled by the use of \u0027scale\u0027, it seems to be coming from fScale, but that should only be used in the constructor and getting the font metrics (which aren\u0027t skewed).",
