      "writtenOn": "2021-01-14T19:11:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The reason for this is that the default color on SkPaint is transparent black and when a shader is in use the alpha of the paint is used to modulate the final value. This allows the user to create a shader for a gradient but then fade it in and out separately. In theory you could just use \"paint.setAlpha(1.0f)\" with a comment about ensuring the gradient is not modulated by alpha here.",
      "revId": "85b37637cbc8e77babcc641bad511013f1b608ea",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
